## What this project is

<!-- One or two sentences. What you are building. Who uses it. -->

## Hard rules for this project

<!-- Rules Claude must never break. Be explicit and specific. Examples below; delete and write your own. -->

- Never write to the production database from this session. Run against the staging copy or ask first.
- Do not commit anything under `/secrets/`. The pre-commit hook blocks this, but belt-and-braces.
- All new API endpoints require corresponding integration tests before merging.

## Key paths and commands

<!-- Where things live; commands you run a lot. -->

- Source: `./src`
- Tests: `./tests`
- Run tests: `pytest -xvs`
- Start dev server: `make dev`

## Memory

Memory files live at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-<you>-<project>/memory/`.
- `topics/` — curated facts per topic.
- `lessons.md` — accumulated error patterns, reviewed at session start.

## Rule priority

```
~/.claude/rules/*.md  → Hard safety (auto-loaded globally)
CLAUDE.md             → This file (auto-loaded per project)
topics/*.md           → Canonical details loaded on demand
```

## Operational defaults

- Prefer editing existing files to creating new ones.
- No performative modesty in writing; state positions directly.
- If about to do something risky or hard to reverse, ask first.
- Log every significant mistake to `topics/lessons.md` with the root-cause-analysis shape from operational rules.
